---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Terms of Service - NotWallet Crypto" 
  description="NotWallet's terms of service - the agreement for using our services"
>
  <Header />
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-nordic-info to-nordic-paper">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-24 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="bg-nordic-paper rounded-nordic shadow-lg p-8 md:p-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-nordic-text mb-6">
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        
        <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-8">
          Last Updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}
        </p>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              These Terms of Service ("Terms") constitute a legally binding agreement between you and NotWallet AB ("NotWallet," "we," "us," or "our") regarding your use of the NotWallet mobile application and related services (collectively, the "Services").
            </p>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              By accessing or using our Services, you agree to be bound by these Terms. If you do not agree to these Terms, you may not access or use our Services.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">2. Description of Services</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              NotWallet is a non-custodial cryptocurrency wallet application that allows users to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 space-y-2">
              <li>Store, send, and receive cryptocurrency assets</li>
              <li>Manage multiple blockchain wallets</li>
              <li>View transaction history and portfolio analytics</li>
              <li>Interact with decentralized applications (dApps)</li>
              <li>Access cryptocurrency market data and information</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              As a non-custodial wallet, NotWallet does not hold, store, or have access to your private keys, seed phrases, or cryptocurrency assets. You maintain full control and responsibility for your digital assets.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">3. Eligibility</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              You must be at least 18 years old to use NotWallet. By using our Services, you represent and warrant that:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 space-y-2">
              <li>You are at least 18 years of age</li>
              <li>You have the legal capacity to enter into these Terms</li>
              <li>You are not prohibited from using our Services under applicable laws</li>
              <li>You will comply with all applicable local, state, national, and international laws and regulations</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">4. Account Security and Responsibility</h2>
            
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-3 mt-6">4.1 Your Responsibilities</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              You are solely responsible for:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 space-y-2">
              <li>Maintaining the confidentiality of your seed phrase, private keys, and passwords</li>
              <li>All activities that occur under your wallet</li>
              <li>Backing up your seed phrase and storing it securely</li>
              <li>Ensuring your device is secure and free from malware</li>
              <li>Verifying the accuracy of all transaction details before confirming</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-3 mt-6">4.2 Loss of Access</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              NotWallet cannot recover, reset, or provide your seed phrase or private keys. If you lose access to your seed phrase or private keys, we cannot help you recover your cryptocurrency assets. You acknowledge and accept this risk.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">5. Prohibited Activities</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              You agree not to engage in any of the following prohibited activities:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 space-y-2">
              <li>Using the Services for any illegal purposes or in violation of any laws</li>
              <li>Attempting to gain unauthorized access to our systems or other users' wallets</li>
              <li>Transmitting viruses, malware, or other harmful code</li>
              <li>Impersonating any person or entity or misrepresenting your affiliation</li>
              <li>Interfering with or disrupting the Services or servers</li>
              <li>Using the Services for money laundering, terrorist financing, or other illicit activities</li>
              <li>Violating any applicable export control or sanctions regulations</li>
              <li>Circumventing any security features or access controls</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">6. Transactions and Fees</h2>
            
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-3 mt-6">6.1 Blockchain Transactions</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              All cryptocurrency transactions are processed on their respective blockchains. Once a transaction is broadcast to the blockchain, it cannot be reversed, canceled, or modified by NotWallet.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-3 mt-6">6.2 Network Fees</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              You are responsible for paying all network fees (gas fees) associated with your transactions. These fees are paid to blockchain validators and are not collected by NotWallet.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-3 mt-6">6.3 Service Fees</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              NotWallet may charge service fees for certain features. Any applicable fees will be clearly disclosed before you complete a transaction.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              The Services, including all content, features, and functionality, are owned by NotWallet and are protected by international copyright, trademark, patent, trade secret, and other intellectual property laws.
            </p>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              You may not reproduce, distribute, modify, create derivative works of, publicly display, or exploit any part of the Services without our express written permission.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">8. Disclaimers and Limitations of Liability</h2>
            
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-3 mt-6">8.1 No Warranties</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              THE SERVICES ARE PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE" WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR IMPLIED. WE DISCLAIM ALL WARRANTIES, INCLUDING MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-3 mt-6">8.2 Cryptocurrency Risks</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              You acknowledge that cryptocurrency transactions and investments carry significant risks, including:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 space-y-2">
              <li>Market volatility and potential loss of value</li>
              <li>Irreversibility of transactions</li>
              <li>Technological vulnerabilities and blockchain risks</li>
              <li>Regulatory uncertainty</li>
              <li>Loss of private keys resulting in permanent loss of assets</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-3 mt-6">8.3 Limitation of Liability</h3>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, NOTWALLET SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, OR ANY LOSS OF PROFITS OR REVENUES, WHETHER INCURRED DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY, OR ANY LOSS OF DATA, USE, GOODWILL, OR OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES.
            </p>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              IN NO EVENT SHALL OUR TOTAL LIABILITY EXCEED THE AMOUNT YOU PAID TO US IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS PRECEDING THE EVENT GIVING RISE TO LIABILITY, OR ONE HUNDRED EUROS (€100), WHICHEVER IS GREATER.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">9. Indemnification</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless NotWallet and its officers, directors, employees, and agents from any claims, liabilities, damages, losses, and expenses arising out of or in any way connected with:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 space-y-2">
              <li>Your use of the Services</li>
              <li>Your violation of these Terms</li>
              <li>Your violation of any rights of another party</li>
              <li>Your violation of any applicable laws or regulations</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">10. Termination</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              We reserve the right to suspend or terminate your access to the Services at any time, with or without notice, for any reason, including if we reasonably believe you have violated these Terms.
            </p>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              You may stop using the Services at any time. As a non-custodial wallet, your cryptocurrency assets remain on the blockchain and accessible with your private keys, regardless of your access to NotWallet.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">11. Governing Law and Dispute Resolution</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of Sweden, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
            </p>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Any disputes arising out of or relating to these Terms or the Services shall be resolved through binding arbitration in Stockholm, Sweden, in accordance with the rules of the Arbitration Institute of the Stockholm Chamber of Commerce.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">12. Changes to Terms</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              We reserve the right to modify these Terms at any time. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated Terms on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.
            </p>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              Your continued use of the Services after any changes to these Terms constitutes your acceptance of the new Terms. If you do not agree to the modified Terms, you must stop using the Services.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">13. Severability</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              If any provision of these Terms is found to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect. The invalid or unenforceable provision shall be replaced with a valid provision that most closely matches the intent of the original provision.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">14. Entire Agreement</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              These Terms, together with our Privacy Policy, constitute the entire agreement between you and NotWallet regarding the Services and supersede all prior agreements and understandings.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-nordic-text mb-4">15. Contact Information</h2>
            <p class="text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 leading-relaxed">
              If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-none text-nordic-text-secondary mb-4 space-y-2">
              <li><strong>Email:</strong> legal@notwallet.app</li>
              <li><strong>Address:</strong> NotWallet AB, Stockholm, Sweden</li>
            </ul>
          </section>
